LEVEL 3 — Advanced (GUI + Compression Ratio)

Features
-> Java Swing GUI
-> File selection
-> Compression ratio display
-> Supports multiple files


1. Java Swing GUI
A graphical interface built using Java Swing instead of terminal output.
What it does:
-> Opens a window (frame)
-> Adds buttons, labels, dialogs
-> Allows user interaction via clicks
Why is it important:
-> Makes your project user-friendly
-> Looks professional on GitHub


2. File Selection
Lets the user choose a file from their system.
What it does:
-> Uses file chooser dialog (JFileChooser)
-> User selects any file (e.g., .txt)
-> Program reads that file
Why is it important:
-> No need to hardcode file paths
-> Works with real user data


3. Compression Ratio Display
Shows how effective your compression is.
Formula:
-> Compression Ratio = Compressed Size / Original Size
Why is it important:
-> Demonstrates performance
-> Very useful in interviews


4. Supports Multiple Files
Allows processing more than one file.
What it does:
-> User can select multiple files
-> Loop through each file and compress it
Why is it important:
-> Makes your tool more powerful
-> Closer to real-world applications
